<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10146535>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Parapenaeopsis cornuta (Kishinouye, 1900), a, c, female cl 22.4 mm (NTOU M02363); b, d, male cl 18.8 mm (NTOU M02363). a, carapace and anterior appendages, lateral view. b, petasma, ventral view. c, thelycum, ventral view. d, right pleopod II, anterior view. Scales: a, c, 5 mm; b, d, 3 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10146535/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10146543>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. a, Parapenaeopsis amicus V.C. Nguyên, 1971, female cl 29.5 mm (NTOU M02417). b, P. cornuta (Kishinouye, 1900), male cl 14.5 mm (NTOU M02357). c, P. hardwickii (Miers, 1878), female cl 30.3 mm (NTOU M02610). d, P. hardwickii (Miers, 1878), male (from Chan & Yu 1986, specimen lost). e, P. tenella (Bate, 1888), female cl 16.7 mm (NTOU M02392). f, P. venusta De Man, 1907, females cl 17.3 mm (NTOU M02395)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10146543/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

